Cadmus was one of the great Slayer of Monsters, only to be later overshadowed by [[Heracles]]. He is the son of King Agenor and Queen Telephassa of Tyre


He later encountered a water dragon in the waters of the Ismenian Spring, which he killed. At Athena's orders, he sowed that dragon's teeth in the ground, from which spran the Spartoi, who helped him build the citadel of Thebes.
